    {
      "id": "ec54f3a5384007f74117805e2e09768acef77334",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-05-06 19:23:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: (1 inline comment)\n\nMaybe he is seeing another problem, but I can see a problem here if the inode was purged by kernel, but the layout lock still exists; then this file is accessed again, it will see an empty layout.\n\nThe above problem can be fixed by removing the above optimization, or clearing bit LVB_READY in md_null_inode().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "246e87df0bdbd857d780cc1dd1f79050c8b939d3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 140,
        "name": "jacques-Charles Lafoucriere",
        "email": "jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr",
        "username": "jcl"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-06 20:53:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: No score\n\nPatch V2 is good, the bug was in my implicit restore code which needed to be adapted to the new released file support (+ this patch)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "419ed4eb65ea54e96dc744c5223a940ec45ce966",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 140,
        "name": "jacques-Charles Lafoucriere",
        "email": "jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr",
        "username": "jcl"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-06 23:19:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAnother issue I suspect. Do you confirm this scenario.\n- file is released\n- client get layout lock on released layout\n- client access data\n- restore triggered and done on a new layout\n- client get the layout lock \nbut as the lvb is not returned with the lock, the old layout (released) is not cleared nor updated (by ll_layout_lock_set()) => client loop on restore request",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
